Package: pickoffgame
Title: Strategies under a pickoff limit in Major League Baseball
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Scott", "Powers", , "scott.powers@rice.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides tools to process, model, and analyze Major League Baseball player tracking data to evaluate strategic adaptation to disengagement limits. The package cleans play-by-play logs alongside runner sprint speeds and catcher arm strengths, fits generalized linear mixed-effects models to estimate capability-adjusted transition probabilities, and implements value iteration algorithms for Markov decision processes and zero-sum sequential games to compute optimal base-running and pickoff strategies.
